(LEAD) N. Korean leader arrives in Beijing for possible summit with Hu
BEIJING, May 25 (Yonhap) -- North Korean leader Kim Jong-il is expected to hold summit talks on Wednesday with Chinese President Hu Jintao that are to focus on bilateral ties, Pyongyang's nuclear programs and Kim's power succession plan to his son. Kim entered the Diaoyutai State Guesthouse in downtown Beijing soon after his special train arrived in the capital's railway station at 9 a.m. after a 19-hour ride through China's eastern areas from Nanjing.